 * \page rd_install_sdl_on_ubuntu_14_10 Install SDL (Ubuntu 14.10)

We use SDL for graphics and sound. Installing SDL on Ubuntu is quite straightforward. Note that you will be prompted for your password upon using '''sudo'''. Type:

\verbatim
sudo apt-get install libsdl1.2-dev libsdl-image1.2-dev libsdl-mixer1.2-dev libsdl-ttf2.0-dev
\endverbatim

